   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Classic RAG Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates a complete RAG pipeline using LangChain + Ollama (local, free)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Prerequisites\n",
    "\n",
    "Install Ollama and pull the required models:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "ollama pull llama3.2\n",
    "ollama pull nomic-embed-text\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install dependencies\n",
    "!pip install langchain langchain-community langchain-ollama chromadb sentence-transformers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from langchain_community.document_loaders import TextLoader\n",
    "from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "from langchain_ollama import OllamaEmbeddings, ChatOllama\n",
    "from langchain_chroma import Chroma\n",
    "from langchain.chains import RetrievalQA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install dependencies\n",
    "!pip install langchain langchain-community langchain-openai chromadb sentence-transformers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from langchain_community.document_loaders import TextLoader\n",
    "from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "from langchain_ollama import OllamaEmbeddings\n",
    "from langchain_community.vectorstores import Chroma\n",
    "from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\n",
    "from langchain.chains import RetrievalQA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set API key\n",
    "os.environ[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"] = \"your-api-key-here\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Load Documents"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create sample document\n",
    "sample_text = \"\"\"\n",
    "Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is an AI framework that enhances \n",
    "Large Language Models by retrieving relevant information from external \n",
    "knowledge bases. RAG addresses key limitations of LLMs including \n",
    "hallucinations, knowledge cutoff, and lack of source attribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "The basic RAG pipeline consists of three components:\n",
    "1. Retrieval: Finding relevant documents\n",
    "2. Augmentation: Adding context to the prompt\n",
    "3. Generation: Producing the final response\n",
    "\n",
    "RAG is particularly useful for:\n",
    "- Question answering systems\n",
    "- Knowledge base chatbots\n",
    "- Enterprise search\n",
    "- Customer support automation\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save sample document\n",
    "with open(\"sample_doc.txt\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(sample_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load document\n",
    "loader = TextLoader(\"sample_doc.txt\")\n",
    "documents = loader.load()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(documents)} document(s)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Split Documents"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split into chunks\n",
    "text_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n",
    "    chunk_size=200,\n",
    "    chunk_overlap=50\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "texts = text_splitter.split_documents(documents)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Created {len(texts)} chunks\")\n",
    "for i, text in enumerate(texts[:3]):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nChunk {i+1}: {text.page_content[:100]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Create Embeddings & Vector Store"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create embeddings\n",
    "embeddings = OllamaEmbeddings(model="nomic-embed-text")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create vector store\n",
    "vectorstore = Chroma.from_documents(\n",
    "    documents=texts,\n",
    "    embedding=embeddings,\n",
    "    persist_directory=\"./chroma_db\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Vector store created successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Create QA Chain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create LLM\n",
    "llm = ChatOpenAI(model=\"gpt-4\", temperature=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create retriever\n",
    "retriever = vectorstore.as_retriever(\n",
    "    search_type=\"similarity\",\n",
    "    search_kwargs={\"k\": 2}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create QA chain\n",
    "qa_chain = RetrievalQA.from_chain_type(\n",
    "    llm=llm,\n",
    "    chain_type=\"stuff\",\n",
    "    retriever=retriever,\n",
    "    return_source_documents=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"QA chain ready!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Query the System"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Ask a question\n",
    "query = \"What are the three components of RAG?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "result = qa_chain.invoke({\"query\": query})\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Question:\", query)\n",
    "print(\"\\nAnswer:\", result[\"result\"])\n",
    "print(\"\\nSource Documents:\")\n",
    "for doc in result[\"source_documents\"]:\n",
    "    print(f\"- {doc.page_content[:80]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Try More Queries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# More example queries\n",
    "queries = [\n",
    "    \"What is RAG used for?\",\n",
    "    \"How does RAG reduce hallucinations?\",\n",
    "    \"What are the limitations of LLMs that RAG addresses?\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for q in queries:\n",
    "    result = qa_chain.invoke({\"query\": q})\n",
    "    print(f\"Q: {q}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"A: {result['result']}\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "- Try with real documents\n",
    "- Experiment with different chunk sizes\n",
    "- Add query optimization techniques\n",
    "- Explore different retrieval strategies"
   ]
  }
